---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Framer vs WordPress 2025: Which Should You Use?',
  description: 'Framer: Modern visual builder, fast workflow, design-first, hosting included. WordPress: Unlimited flexibility, massive ecosystem, you own everything, hosting separate. Choose Framer for design and speed. WordPress for flexibility and long-term ownership.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Framer vs WordPress', 'Framer review', 'WordPress alternative', 'website builder comparison', 'no-code'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#0055FF]/5 to-[#0099FF]/5 py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#0055FF] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Website Builder Comparison · 2025
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Framer vs WordPress
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Framer is the modern visual builder. Design-first approach, incredibly fast workflow, everything included. WordPress is the flexible CMS. Power unlimited, massive ecosystem, you own everything. Different tools for different priorities. Here's how to choose.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Choose Framer if you want beautiful design fast and don't need complex functionality. Choose WordPress if you need flexibility, specific plugins, or want full ownership. Framer is easier for non-technical users. WordPress can do anything but requires more technical skill.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Quick Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Framer</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">WordPress</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Ease of Use</td>
            <td class="p-14">Easy, visual builder</td>
            <td class="p-14">Moderate, learning curve</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Design Flexibility</td>
            <td class="p-14">High within system</td>
            <td class="p-14">Unlimited with themes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">CMS</td>
            <td class="p-14">Built-in, powerful</td>
            <td class="p-14">The core feature</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">E-commerce</td>
            <td class="p-14">Basic via Stripe/WooCommerce</td>
            <td class="p-14">WooCommerce plugin</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Hosting</td>
            <td class="p-14">Included ($0 custom domain on paid)</td>
            <td class="p-14">Separate (self-hosted or managed)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Plugins</td>
            <td class="p-14">Integrations only</td>
            <td class="p-14">60,000+ plugins</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Ownership</td>
            <td class="p-14">Platform dependent</td>
            <td class="p-14">You own everything</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Code Export</td>
            <td class="p-14">Yes (React/CSS)</td>
            <td class="p-14">PHP (open source)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Learning Curve</td>
            <td class="p-14">Low</td>
            <td class="p-14">Moderate to high</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Best For</td>
            <td class="p-14">Designers, portfolios, marketing sites</td>
            <td class="p-14">Complex sites, blogs, e-commerce</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Framer Deep Dive -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Framer Does Well
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Visual Design System</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer's visual builder is exceptional. Click and edit anything. Drag and drop components. Real-time preview. The interface feels like design software, not a website builder.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> You can create professional designs quickly without CSS knowledge. The learning curve is shallow. What you see is what you get.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Speed of Workflow</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Everything is fast in Framer. Building, editing, publishing. No waiting for page reloads. No complex configuration. Just design and publish.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> You can iterate quickly. Test ideas. Make changes. The friction between idea and execution is minimal.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Built-in CMS</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Content management is built-in. Blog posts, portfolio items, product pages. Create collections, define fields, add content. Simple but powerful.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> You don't need separate plugins or configuration. CMS works out of the box with custom fields and dynamic pages.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Modern, Fast Sites</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer sites are fast by default. Optimized images, code splitting, caching. Google PageSpeed scores are excellent without optimization work.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Site speed affects SEO and user experience. Framer handles technical optimization automatically.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Responsive by Default</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Design once, works everywhere. Mobile, tablet, desktop layouts adapt automatically. Fine-tune breakpoints when needed.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Mobile traffic is 60%+. Your site must work perfectly on all devices. Framer makes this easy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Code Export</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Export your site as React/CSS code. Host anywhere if you want. Deploy to Vercel, Netlify, your own server.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> You're not locked into Framer hosting. You can leave if needed. Export and deploy elsewhere.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WordPress Deep Dive -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What WordPress Does Well
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Unlimited Flexibility</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">WordPress can do anything. Blog, e-commerce, membership, forum, LMS, booking. Any functionality you can imagine exists as a plugin.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Complex requirements are no problem. Need a specific feature? There's a plugin for that. Or build custom functionality.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Massive Ecosystem</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">60,000+ plugins. 10,000+ themes. Developers, designers, agencies everywhere. Solutions exist for every problem.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> You're never stuck. Someone has solved your problem before. Find the solution, install it, customize.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">You Own Everything</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">WordPress is open source. You own your content, your design, your data. Host where you want. Change what you want.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> No platform can shut you down. No rent increases. Complete control and ownership long-term.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">E-commerce Power</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">WooCommerce is the most popular e-commerce plugin. Full online store functionality. Inventory, payments, shipping, taxes.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> If you're selling products, WooCommerce is mature and powerful. Extensive extension ecosystem.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Blogging Native</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">WordPress started as blogging software. Content creation, categories, tags, comments - all built-in and mature.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> If content marketing is your strategy, WordPress is purpose-built for it. No workarounds needed.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Developer Access</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Full code access. PHP, HTML, CSS, JavaScript - modify anything. Custom themes, custom plugins, full control.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> If you have development resources or hire developers, WordPress can be customized without limits.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Pricing Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Framer Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Free:</strong> Framer branding, limited features</li>
          <li>• <strong>Basic ($16/month or $144/year):</strong> Remove branding, custom domain, 5 CMS items</li>
          <li>• <strong>Pro ($30/month or $276/year):</strong> 50 CMS items, no Framer branding on forms</li>
          <li>• <strong>Dynamic ($85/month or $828/year):</strong> Unlimited CMS items, 3 team members</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Hosting included:</strong> No separate hosting costs. Custom domain free on paid plans.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">WordPress Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Software:</strong> Free forever (open source)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Hosting:</strong> $3-50/month depending on host</li>
          <li>• <strong>Domain:</strong> $10-15/year</li>
          <li>• <strong>Premium themes:</strong> $50-200 one-time</li>
          <li>• <strong>Premium plugins:</strong> $50-500/year</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Hosting separate:</strong> You pay for hosting separately. WordPress.com offers hosting but is limited.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- When to Choose -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      When to Choose Each
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Choose Framer If</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>You're a designer:</strong> Visual workflow fits how you work</li>
          <li>• <strong>You need a portfolio:</strong> Showcase sites are Framer's strength</li>
          <li>• <strong>You want speed:</strong> Build and launch quickly</li>
          <li>• <strong>You're non-technical:</strong> No code required</li>
          <li>• <strong>You want included hosting:</strong> One price, everything included</li>
          <li>• <strong>You care about design:</strong> Modern aesthetics out of the box</li>
          <li>• <strong>Your needs are straightforward:</strong> Marketing site, blog, simple CMS</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Choose WordPress If</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>You need flexibility:</strong> Complex functionality requirements</li>
          <li>• <strong>You're building an online store:</strong> WooCommerce is mature</li>
          <li>• <strong>You blog heavily:</strong> WordPress is blogging native</li>
          <li>• <strong>You want ownership:</strong> Own your data and platform</li>
          <li>• <strong>You have technical resources:</strong> Developer access and customization</li>
          <li>• <strong>You plan long-term:</strong> WordPress sites can scale indefinitely</li>
          <li>• <strong>Budget is a concern:</strong> Software is free, pay only for hosting</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Framer and WordPress solve different problems. Framer is the modern design tool. WordPress is the flexible CMS. Neither is universally better. Choose based on your priorities.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Framer for:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Visual design workflow</li>
        <li>• Speed to launch</li>
        <li>• Simple to moderate complexity</li>
        <li>• Non-technical users</li>
        <li>• Portfolios and marketing sites</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose WordPress for:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Unlimited flexibility</li>
        <li>• Complex functionality</li>
        <li>• E-commerce with WooCommerce</li>
        <li>• Long-term ownership</li>
        <li>• Technical users willing to learn</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700"><strong>Can't decide?</strong> Start with Framer. If you outgrow it, export your code and migrate to WordPress. Starting simpler and upgrading beats starting complex and regretting it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related Comparisons
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/framer-vs-webflow" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer vs Webflow</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Modern builders compared</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/webflow-vs-wordpress" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Webflow vs WordPress</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">No-code vs open source</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
